  <title>Determine which version of GNOME is running</title>

  <p>You can determine the version of GNOME that is running on your system by
  going to the <gui>Details/About</gui> panel in <gui>Settings</gui>.</p>

  <steps>
    <item>
      <p>Open the <gui xref="shell-introduction#overview">Overview</gui> and
      start typing <gui>About</gui>.</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>Click on <gui>About</gui> to open the panel.</p>
      <p>A window appears showing information about your system, including your
      distributionâ€™s name and the GNOME version.</p>
    </item>
  </steps>

